SUMMARY:Spring into Sustainability: Eco Consciousness Ahead of Earth Day
DESCRIPTION:Calling all teens as we head toward Earth Day!\nJoin us for an afternoon of learning about how the small choices we make every day\, like food\, water\, and energy use\, can grow into bigger changes for our community and environment. \nRegisterEvent DetailsWe will be making seed bombs using native wildflower seeds that support pollinators and beneficial insects. These seed bombs will be distributed to our community to encourage others to make a positive impact on our environment. \nA pizza lunch will be provided. We are happy to provide volunteer hour verification for teens for this program upon request. \nThis event is part of the Social Action Sundays for Teens series hosted by Congregation Shaarey Zedek.
URL:https://adamah.org/event/detroit-teens-spring-sustainability/
LOCATION:Congregation Shaarey Zedek\, 27375 Bell Road\, Southfield\, Michigan\, 48034\, United States
CATEGORIES:Detroit,Earth Day
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Earth-Day.jpg
END:VEVENT
