SUMMARY:From Earth to Bread: Passover and the Grain Harvest
DESCRIPTION:Explore the Jewish relationship to bread hands-on as we enjoy our last chametz before Pesach\nJoin Malkhut and Adamah NY in LIC to prepare for the holiday of Passover with an afternoon of learning\, bread making and eating together.  \n\nRegisterEvent Details \n\nHannah Kahn Glass from Adamah NY will guide us in a joyful\, hands-on experience exploring bread making and the spiritual and agriculture process Jews go through from Passover through Shavuot. \nTogether we’ll learn\, create\, and connect with the traditions that link the foods we eat to the rhythms of the Jewish calendar. After learning with Hannah and Student Rabbi Emily Herzlin\, we’ll gather to enjoy delicious chametz-inspired treats. Feel free to bring your own favorite chametz dish to share as we celebrate learning\, community\, and the flavors of the season together. \n\nLearn more and register here.
URL:https://adamah.org/event/pre-pesach-event-in-lic/
LOCATION:Small Renew\, Long Island City\, NY
CATEGORIES:New York,Pesach
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Untitled-design-4.png
END:VEVENT
