UID:24407-1774440000-1774440000@adamah.org
SUMMARY:Moving Climate Action Forward: A Two-Part Intensive
DESCRIPTION:Location will be emailed to registrants prior to program date. \nSession 1: March 25\, Wednesday at 12pm ET/9am PT\nSession 2: April 15\, Wednesday at 12pm ET/9am PT  \n\n\n \nClimate action inside a Jewish organization isn’t always a technical challenge\, it’s also a leadership one.\nThis two-part intensive is designed to give you practical skills and peer support to lead climate action in your organization with more confidence and clarity.  \nRegisterEvent DetailsWhether you’re just getting started or you’ve already mapped out a plan\, the hardest part is often the same: building momentum\, navigating competing priorities\, and bringing others along with you. \nOur new two-part intensive\, Moving Climate Action Forward\, is designed to give you the practical skills to build momentum\, engage stakeholders\, and keep making progress. You’ll leave with a stronger sense of how to approach your work\, how to engage stakeholders\, and how to keep moving forward when things get hard. \nSessions are interactive and grounded in real challenges. Come ready to think\, share\, and learn alongside peers from across the Jewish community. This is a cohort style program with limited space\, register to claim your spot!\n\n\nSession 1:\nBuilding your approach to climate action: how to think about where you are\, where you want to go\, and how to make progress. \nSession 2:\nNavigating the people side: stakeholder buy-in\, common pitfalls\, and how to stay on track when momentum stalls. \n\nNote: This program is open to members of the Jewish Climate Leadership Coalition. Membership is free! Learn more at www.adamah.org/coalition or email us at coalition@adamah.org.
URL:https://adamah.org/event/moving-climate-action-forward/
CATEGORIES:Coalition
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/ClimateMarch.jpg
END:VEVENT
