SUMMARY:Adamah Adventures: Spring Break Camp Days
DESCRIPTION:Dates: March 30\, 31\, April 1\, 6\, 7\nTime: 9:00am-3:00pm \n\n\n \nNature Connection\, Community Service and Fun!\nAdamah Adventures: Spring Break Camp Days is a NEW program for elementary and middle school-age children near Detroit. \nRegisterEvent Details \nGet a taste of summer Nature Camp this spring!\nImmerse in Jewish nature connections\, wilderness skill-building and crafting\, and environmental stewardship projects!\nThis is an educational and community building program through which young people can engage in meaningful community service\, cultivate Jewish identity and community\, and build the foundation for a lifetime of Jewish environmental stewardship. \nDates: March 30\, 31\, April 1\, 6\, 7\, 9:00am-3:00pm. \nThis offering is geared toward 3rd-7th grade students at a cost of $85 per day (limited scholarships and sibling discounts available). \nWe will provide a morning and afternoon snack and ask that you please bring a packed lunch. \n\nSample Day: \n\n9am – Drop off\n9:15am – Welcome and opening circle\n10am – Morning Activity block & Snack\n12pm – Lunch\n12:30 Nature Chuggim/Open play Stations\n1pm Afternoon Activity block\n2:30 – Snack\, clean up\, closing circle\n3pm – Pickup\n\nEach day of camp will earn students at least one hour of environmental service work. \nThis program is made possible by generous support from:
URL:https://adamah.org/event/adamah-adventures-spring-break-camp-days/
LOCATION:Huntington Woods Library and Cultural Center\, 26415 Scotia Road\, Huntington Woods\, MI\, 48070
CATEGORIES:Detroit
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/camp-blowing-shofar-in-woods.jpg
END:VEVENT
