SUMMARY:Sofrut (Hebrew calligraphy) Workshop: 6 Part Series
DESCRIPTION:Exact location TBD \n\n\n \nLearn Hebrew Caligraphy\nJoin us for a six-part Sofrut ‘Hebrew Calligraphy’ series\, exploring the ancient ancestral skill of creating feather quills\, oak galls\, and the living language of Hebrew letters. \n\nRegister TodayEvent DetailsLong before we were ever called the People of the Book\, we were a people of hands\, ink\, and parchment. Writing Hebrew was an ancestral craft\, rooted in the living world\, shaped by feather quills\, oak galls\, and patient attention. \nJoin us for a six-part Sofrut\, ‘Hebrew Calligraphy’ series\, exploring these ancient skills. Together\, we will learn how to make oak gall ink from the land\, cut our own feather quills\, and practice the sacred art of forming Hebrew letters by hand. This is a slow\, embodied invitation into relationship with Hebrew as a living language and a sacred form. \nThis series is perfect for those seeking to deepen their connection to Hebrew and Jewish tradition\, as well as for those encountering the Aleph Bet for the very first time. No prior experience is necessary\, only curiosity\, care\, and a willingness to learn with your hands. \nMeeting Dates (Tuesdays\, 7:00-9:00 p.m) \n\nApril 14\nApri 21\nApril 28\nMay 5\nMay 12\nMay 19
URL:https://adamah.org/event/sofrut-hebrew-calligraphy-workshop-6-part-series/
LOCATION:Chochmat Halev\, 2215 Prince St\, Berkeley\, 94705\, United States
CATEGORIES:San Francisco Bay Area
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/featherworkshop-e1770966476535.jpg
END:VEVENT
