SUMMARY:Yom HaZikaron 2026: Remembering Those We Lost
DESCRIPTION:Park Heights (location provided upon registration) \n\n\n \nJoin Baltimore’s Shinshinim and Shlichim\nHonor the memory of Israelis who were killed in acts of terror or who fell in battle through hearing their stories from the perspective of those who knew them. \nRegisterEvent Details \nJoin Pearlstone\, The Associated\, Jewish Educational Services\, and The Baltimore Jewish Council for an evening of commemoration and storytelling for Yom HaZikaron. Honor the memory of Israelis who were killed in acts of terror or who fell in battle through hearing their stories from the perspective of those who knew them. Then mark with us the transition from Yom HaZikaron to Yom HaAtzmaut\, as we remember that our celebration of Israel’s independence is inseparable from the sacrifices that made it possible. \nQuestions? Contact Kate McDonald (kmcdonald@baltjc.org).
URL:https://adamah.org/event/baltmore-yom-hazikaron-2026/
CATEGORIES:Baltimore,Holidays,Pearlstone,Pearlstone Education
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://adamah.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Yom-Hazikaron-750x375-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
